  "opening_lines": [
    {
      "line": 1,
      "text": "Mee Foot NIIAL"
    },
    {
      "line": 4,
      "text": "N SOME CASES, THE"
    },
    {
      "line": 6,
      "text": "evaluations in this"
    },
    {
      "line": 8,
      "text": "Catalog are probably"
    },
    {
      "line": 10,
      "text": "inadequate. All will"
    },
    {
      "line": 11,
      "text": "become dated at some point."
    },
    {
      "line": 12,
      "text": "If you’re sure that something"
    },
    {
      "line": 13,
      "text": "you know is better than what"
    },
    {
      "line": 14,
      "text": "we've reviewed, have at us,"
    },
    {
      "line": 15,
      "text": "so that the next Catalog will"
    },
    {
      "line": 16,
      "text": "be more accurate at pointing"
    },
    {
      "line": 17,
      "text": "at excellence."
    },
    {
      "line": 20,
      "text": "Our standard advice for writing a"
    },
    {
      "line": 21,
      "text": "review goes like this:"
    },
    {
      "line": 24,
      "text": "® Give the kind of information you"
    },
    {
      "line": 26,
      "text": "would like to get. This should in-"
    },
    {
      "line": 28,
      "text": "clude what the item is good for,"
    },
    {
      "line": 30,
      "text": "how it compares with others, and some"
    },
    {
      "line": 31,
      "text": "clue as to how competent you are to judge."
    },
    {
      "line": 32,
      "text": "Avoid comments like “This is a good book.”"
    },
    {
      "line": 33,
      "text": "Prove it."
    },
    {
      "line": 36,
      "text": "© Think of yourself as writing a letter to an"
    },
    {
      "line": 37,
      "text": "intelligent, uninformed friend about some-"
    },
    {
      "line": 38,
      "text": "thing that is interesting/important to you."
    },
    {
      "line": 40,
      "text": "Be succinct. A paragraph is frequently enough."
    },
    {
      "line": 41,
      "text": "Introduce the item and get out of the way."
    },
    {
      "line": 42,
      "text": "You don’t have to analyze it, just tell us why"
    },
    {
      "line": 43,
      "text": "you love it and why we should run it."
    },
    {
      "line": 46,
      "text": "© Suppliers are invited to suggest their own"
    },
    {
      "line": 47,
      "text": "goods. Samples or review copies are wel-"
    },
    {
      "line": 48,
      "text": "comed; response is not predictable. We ask"
    },
    {
      "line": 49,
      "text": "for no payment and will accept none. We"
    },
    {
      "line": 50,
      "text": "serve as an information exchange and owe"
    },
    {
      "line": 51,
      "text": "only accuracy to suppliers."
    },
    {
      "line": 54,
      "text": "© We pay for everything we print, including"
    },
    {
      "line": 55,
      "text": "complaint letters. You get $20 for a review"
    },
    {
      "line": 56,
      "text": "and $20 for first suggestion ($40 if you pro-"
    },
    {
      "line": 57,
      "text": "vide both). Cartoons and photographs earn $30"
    },
    {
      "line": 58,
      "text": "and up. Payment for an article typically ranges"
    },
    {
      "line": 59,
      "text": "from $100 to $500, depending on wonderful-"
    }
  ]
